# Runner-image profiles. Each line is `<xcode-version> [active|inactive]`;
# the annotation defaults to `active` when absent. `#`-prefixed lines
# are comments.
#
# **Active** profiles get rebuilt on every `release-runner-image` run
# (any commit under `infra/runner-image/**`). Use sparingly — each
# active profile adds ~30 min to the release wall-clock on the
# singleton vm-image-builder host. Keep this to the Xcodes the fleet
# is currently rolling onto.
#
# **Inactive** profiles stay published in GHCR (customers can still
# pin to them) but only rebuild on demand:
#
#     gh workflow run runner-image.yml -f xcode_version=26.X.Y
#
# Use this when there's a runner-agent / dispatch-loop / launchd
# change you want to roll into an older Xcode profile without
# ratcheting the every-commit cost.
#
# The **first active line** is the default profile — the chart's
# `runnersFleet.runnerImage` digest pin tracks it.
26.5
26.4.1
